CEOs on LinkedIn are having a full-blown episode — and they’re documenting it in real time.

Apparently:
• If you don’t check Slack on vacation, you “don’t care”
• Working 9 days straight is a flex, not a warning sign
• December 26th is now a competitive sport
• Getting up at 3:30 a.m. makes you elite
• Posting about working is working

Every single post is some variation of:
“I’m not better than you… I just never stop.”

And somehow all of these people post on the same days, at the same times, saying the same things, with the same
title: CEOS ON LINKEDIN ARE COOKED!
